<br>
Know this Apep, my skin is blue like yours.  My blood boils like yours.  I may not be as seasoned as you and your army, but I will be there in defense of those who you mean to enslave.  By making war on the Gnomes without the full support of Neriak's c'rintri, you are only proving what the light races have said about our people all along, we are egotistical, self-serving, and twisted beings.  I am living proof that that the Teir'dal are capable of being more than that, and the other Teir'dal like Didi who have pledged their lives to defend the Gnomes from genocide demonstrate that we Teir'dal have the capability to break away from the stigma that surrounds us.<br>
<br>
We all have the capability to become more than the sum of our parts.  The question is:  aside from your display of arms and magic, are you powerful enough to overcome your personal demons?<br>
<br>
Cronadan Do`Bluth<br>
